{%- block title -%}
	Download
{%- endblock %}
{% block content %}

<p>
	You want to try out <span class="algo">Firm</span>?
	<span class="algo">Firm</span> itself is just a library, so you probably want our C frontend <tt>cparser</tt> as well.
</p>
<p>
	We provide <a href="#Git">git instructions</a>, a <a href="#Tarball">tarball</a> and <a href="#Ubuntu">Ubuntu packages</a>.
</p>

<h2 id="Git">Git</h2>
<p>Check it out with git:
</p>
{% code 'bash' %}
$ git clone http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/git/cparser.git
$ cd cparser
{% endcode %}
<p>Additionally, we need the <span class="algo">Firm</span> library, which is included as a submodule.
</p>
{% code 'bash' %}
$ git submodule update --init
{% endcode %}
<p>Now build everything. You need a C compiler, GNU Make, Perl, and Python.
</p>
{% code 'bash' %}
$ make
{% endcode %}
</p><p>Now you should have a working binary.
</p>
{% code 'bash' %}
$ build/debug/cparser --version
{% endcode %}
<p>Our compiler tries to be a drop in replacement for GCC, so it supports the same arguments.
Try it on some C99 code, like <tt>cparser -Wall -O3 test.c</tt> or <tt>make CC=cparser</tt>.
</p>
<p>
	Note that on 64-bit systems, you have to additionally pass <tt>-m32</tt> because <tt>cparser</tt> generates 32-bit code by default.
</p>
<p>If you find bugs, please report them in our <a class="external text" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/~firm/bugs/">issue tracker</a>.
</p>

<h2 id="Tarball">Source Release</h2>
<p>You can download the source tarball here:
</p>
<pre><a class="external free" href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/libfirm/files/libfirm/">https://sourceforge.net/projects/libfirm/files/libfirm/</a>
</pre>
<p>Afterwards a usual <tt>./configure &amp;&amp; make</tt> will do the rest.
</p>

<h2 id="Ubuntu">Ubuntu Packages</h2>
<p>An experimental repository for Ubuntu karmic is available, which contains a libfirm-dev package.
The packages were not checked by Ubuntu developers, so use <b>at your own risk</b>.
Add the following to your sources.list:
</p>
<pre>deb <a class="external free" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/~zwinkau/repo/Ubuntu">http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/~zwinkau/repo/Ubuntu</a> karmic IPD
deb-src <a class="external free" href="http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/~zwinkau/repo/Ubuntu">http://pp.ipd.kit.edu/~zwinkau/repo/Ubuntu</a> karmic IPD
</pre>
<p>The reason for the libfirm-dev package is mostly as a build dependency for <a class="external text" href="http://cparser.sourceforge.net/">cparser</a>, which is also in the repository.
</p>

{% endblock %}
